hwISIS.description: The private ISIS MIB contains objects to manage the ISIS routing protocol private objects in pure IP environment.

hwIsisSysTable.name: hwIsisSysTable
hwIsisSysTable.description: The set of instances of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

hwIsisSysEntry.name: hwIsisSysEntry
hwIsisSysEntry.description: Each row defines Huawei priviate information specific to a single instance of the protocol existing on the system.

hwIsisSysWrongSysTypes.name: hwIsisSysWrongSysTypes
hwIsisSysWrongSysTypes.description: Number of Times Wrong System Types requested for Adjacencies.

hwIsisSysAuthAreaRecvPwd1.name: hwIsisSysAuthAreaRecvPwd1
hwIsisSysAuthAreaRecvPwd1.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key in Level 1 Link State Packets receivied from the neighbouring systems, whenever the value of isisSysAuthAreaType has a value of plaintext or md5. Authentication of the received LSP is successful, when authentication is successful on using any one of the RecvPwd?. A modification of isisSysAuthAreaType does not modify the hwIsisSysAuthAreaRecvPwd1 value. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

hwIsisSysSetLSDBOload.name: hwIsisSysSetLSDBOload
hwIsisSysSetLSDBOload.description: Setting this object to 'true' forces the system to set the overload bit in its non-pseudonode LSPs. The result will be that no paths through this system are seen by other systems in the IS-IS area.

hwIsisCircTable.name: hwIsisCircTable
hwIsisCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by each instance of Integrated IS-IS on this system.

hwIsisCircEntry.name: hwIsisCircEntry
hwIsisCircEntry.description: An isisCircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

hwIsisCircFuncState.name: hwIsisCircFuncState
hwIsisCircFuncState.description: The functional state of the circuit. This specifies whether the circuit is currently active or not.

hwIsisCircLevel.name: hwIsisCircLevel
hwIsisCircLevel.description: The level of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

hwIsisCircVersionSkews.name: hwIsisCircVersionSkews
hwIsisCircVersionSkews.description: The number of PDUs of different version was received

hwIsisCircStateChanges.name: hwIsisCircStateChanges
hwIsisCircStateChanges.description: The number of times the circuit has changed the state.

hwIsisCircAreaMismatches.name: hwIsisCircAreaMismatches
hwIsisCircAreaMismatches.description: The number PDUs from an unrecognised area was received

hwIsisIPReachAddr.name: hwIsisIPReachAddr
hwIsisIPReachAddr.description: ISIS local interface IP address information.

hwIsisIPRATable.name: hwIsisIPRATable
hwIsisIPRATable.description: The table of IP Reachable Addresses to networks, subnetworks or hosts either manually configured or learned from another protocol.

hwIsisIPRAEntry.name: hwIsisIPRAEntry
hwIsisIPRAEntry.description: Each entry defines an IP Reachable Address to a network, subnetwork or host.

hwIsisIPRAFuncState.name: hwIsisIPRAFuncState
hwIsisIPRAFuncState.description: The functional state of the IP reachable address. This specifies whether this RA is active or not.

hwIsisIPRANextHopAddress.name: hwIsisIPRANextHopAddress
hwIsisIPRANextHopAddress.description: The Next Hop IP Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

hwIsisCorruptedLSPDetected.name: hwIsisCorruptedLSPDetected
hwIsisCorruptedLSPDetected.description: The Corrupted LSP Detected Notification is generated when a corrupted Link State PDU is detected in memory.

hwIsisCorruptedLSPReceived.name: hwIsisCorruptedLSPReceived
hwIsisCorruptedLSPReceived.description: The Corrupted LSP Received Notification is generated when a corrupted Link State PDU is Received. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysCorrLSPscounter.

hwIsisLSPL1DatabaseOverload.name: hwIsisLSPL1DatabaseOverload
hwIsisLSPL1DatabaseOverload.description: The LSP L1 Database Overload Notification is generated when the l1State of the system changes between On and Waiting or Waiting and On. The isisSysL1State argument is set to indicate the resulting state, and in the case of Waiting the isisSysID is set to indicate the source of the LSP which precipitated the overload. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads counter.

hwIsisLSPL2DatabaseOverload.name: hwIsisLSPL2DatabaseOverload
hwIsisLSPL2DatabaseOverload.description: The LSP L2 Database Overload Notification is generated when the l2State of the system changes between On and Waiting or Waiting and On. The isisSysL2State argument is set to indicate the resulting state, and in the case of Waiting the isisSysID is set to indicate the source of the LSP which precipitated the overload. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads counter.

hwIsisAuthenticationFailure.name: hwIsisAuthenticationFailure
hwIsisAuthenticationFailure.description: Generated when a PDU is received with an incorrect Authentication information field

hwIsisWrongSysType.name: hwIsisWrongSysType
hwIsisWrongSysType.description: Generated when a Adjacency Request for Wrong/unsupported adjacency type is made.

hwIsisVersionSkew.name: hwIsisVersionSkew
hwIsisVersionSkew.description: Generated when a PDU of Wrong/different version is received

hwIsisIDFieldLengthMismatch.name: hwIsisIDFieldLengthMismatch
hwIsisIDFieldLengthMismatch.description: The hwIsisIDFieldLengthMismatch Notification is generated when a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving Intermediate system. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.

hwIsisAreaMismatch.name: hwIsisAreaMismatch
hwIsisAreaMismatch.description: Generated when a PDU is received from Wrong/different area not recognised by this system

hwIsisMaxAreaAddrMismatch.name: hwIsisMaxAreaAddrMismatch
hwIsisMaxAreaAddrMismatch.description: Generated when a PDU is received from Wrong/different area not recognised by this system

hwIsisManualAddressDroppedFromArea.name: hwIsisManualAddressDroppedFromArea
hwIsisManualAddressDroppedFromArea.description: The Manual Address Dropped From Area Notification is generated when one of the manualAreaAddresses (specified on this system) is ignored when computing partitionAreaAddresses or areaAddresses because there are more than MaximumAreaAddresses distinct Area Addresses. The hwIsisTrapDroppedAreaAddr argument is set to the ignored Area Address. It is generated once for each Area Address in manualAreaAddresses which is dropped. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysManAddrDropFromAreas counter.

hwIsisAttemptToExceedMaximumSequenceNumb.name: hwIsisAttemptToExceedMaximumSequenceNumber
hwIsisAttemptToExceedMaximumSequenceNumb.description: The Attempt To Exceed Maximum Sequence Number Notification is generated when an attempt is made to increment the sequence number of an LSP beyond the maximum sequence number. Following the generation of this event the operation of the Routeing state machine shall be disabled for atleast (MaxAge + ZeroAgeLifetime) seconds. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums counter.

hwIsisSequenceNumberSkip.name: hwIsisSequenceNumberSkip
hwIsisSequenceNumberSkip.description: The Sequence Number Skipped Notification is generated when the sequence number of an LSP is incremented by more than one. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysSeqNumSkips counter.

hwIsisOwnLSPPurge.name: hwIsisOwnLSPPurge
hwIsisOwnLSPPurge.description: The Own LSP Purged Notification is generated when a zero aged copy of a system's own LSP is received from some other system. This represents an erroneous attempt to purge the local system's LSP. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisSysOwnLSPPurges counter.

hwIsisCircuitChange.name: hwIsisCircuitChange
hwIsisCircuitChange.description: The Circuit Change Notification is generated when the state of the Circuit changes from On to Off or from Off to On. The relative order of events relating to the same Circuit must be preserved.

hwIsisAdjacencyStateChange.name: hwIsisAdjacencyStateChange
hwIsisAdjacencyStateChange.description: The Adjacency State Change Notification is generated when the state of an Adjacency on the Circuit changes from Up to Down or Down to Up. For these purposes the states Up and Up/dormant are considered to be Up, and any other state is considered to be Down. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisCircAdjChanges counter.

hwIsisInitializationFailure.name: hwIsisInitializationFailure
hwIsisInitializationFailure.description: The Initialisation Failure Notification is generated when an attempt to initialise with an adjacent system fails as a result of either Version Skew or Area Mismatch. In the case of Version Skew, the Adjacent system argument is not present. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisCircInitFails counter.

hwIsisRejectedAdjacency.name: hwIsisRejectedAdjacency
hwIsisRejectedAdjacency.description: The Rejected Adjacency Notification is generated when an attempt to create a new adjacency is rejected, because of a lack of resources. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisCircRejAdjs counter.

hwIsisLanL1DesignatedIntermediateSystemC.name: hwIsisLanL1DesignatedIntermediateSystemChange
hwIsisLanL1DesignatedIntermediateSystemC.description: The LAN L1 Designated Intermediate System Change Notification is generated when the local system either elects itself or resigns as being the LAN L1 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. The relative order of these events must be preserved. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisCircLANL1DesISChanges counter.

hwIsisLanL2DesignatedIntermediateSystemC.name: hwIsisLanL2DesignatedIntermediateSystemChange
hwIsisLanL2DesignatedIntermediateSystemC.description: The LAN L2 Designated Intermediate System Change Notification is generated when the local system either elects itself or resigns as being the LAN L2 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. The relative order of these events must be preserved. The occurance of this event is counted by the isisCircLANL2DesISChanges counter.

hwIsisTrapTable.name: hwIsisTrapTable
hwIsisTrapTable.description: The set of Values needed for trap support.

hwIsisTrapEntry.name: hwIsisTrapEntry
hwIsisTrapEntry.description: Each row defines information specific to a Trap information

hwIsisTrapSysInstance.name: hwIsisTrapSysInstance
hwIsisTrapSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

hwIsisTrapDroppedAreaAddr.name: hwIsisTrapDroppedAreaAddr
hwIsisTrapDroppedAreaAddr.description: The Area Address that was dropped by the system when the count of area addresses exceeded the Maximum .

hwIsisTrapCorruptedLSPID.name: hwIsisTrapCorruptedLSPID
hwIsisTrapCorruptedLSPID.description: The ID of the LSP that was found to be Corrupted.

hwIsisTrapSysIDLength.name: hwIsisTrapSysIDLength
hwIsisTrapSysIDLength.description: The Length of the SystemID of current system.

hwIsisTrapAuthErrorInfo.name: hwIsisTrapAuthErrorInfo
hwIsisTrapAuthErrorInfo.description: The Information Pertaining to the Authentication error.

hwIsisTrapRecdVersion.name: hwIsisTrapRecdVersion
hwIsisTrapRecdVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol that was received.

hwIsisTrapRecdMaxAreaAddr.name: hwIsisTrapRecdMaxAreaAddr
hwIsisTrapRecdMaxAreaAddr.description: The Max Area Address Count in a received PDU.

hwIsisCompliance.name: hwIsisCompliance
hwIsisCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities implementing the Huawei ISIS MIB

hwIsisNotificationGroup.name: hwIsisNotificationGroup
hwIsisNotificationGroup.description: A collection of isis notification objects.

hwIsisTrapInfoGroup.name: hwIsisTrapInfoGroup
hwIsisTrapInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects providing trap records.
